text: St. Charles County is a county in Missouri, United States. The county seat is St. Charles. In 2020, 405,262 people lived there, making it the third-most populous county in Missouri. St. Charles County is part of the St. Louis, MO- IL Metropolitan Statistical Area and has many of the city's northwestern suburbs. ==References== Category:1812 establishments in Missouri Territory Category:Missouri counties
title: St. Charles County, Missouri
